  "texts": [
    "For example, the concept \"prostate cancer\",, \"lesion\", \"prostate specific antigen\", \"elevated PSA\" would have little distinctive capabilities within a corpus of all prostate cancer patients.",
    "Modern LLMs rely on word-piece tokenizers that meet the challenge of out-of-vocabulary token by chopping up the word into smaller foundational pieces such as \"carcinoma\" may be chopped into \"car_\" and \"_cinoma\".",
    "However, we argue that chopping up important domain specific terms into multiple tokens may hinder model's focus on learning about the whole clinical terms and their context.",
    "A passage full of relevant medical information containing N words may be divided in M tokens when M>>N.",
    "In extreme cases, M may exceed the length of the context window causing the model to ignore some information."
  ],
